name: US National Database of Childcare Prices:2008-2018
description: The National Database of Childcare Prices (NDCP) is a new data source that is the most complete federal source of county-level childcare prices in the United States. The NDCP provides daycare price statistics by childcare provider type and child age (ages 0-12). Childcare prices for the most current year of data collection, 2018, are shown, as well as adjusted for inflation to 2022 real dollars.
